1. Type of tags:
- lightweight: 
  - temporary
  - like a branch name, point to commit
- annotated:
  - like an object
  - recommended way to tag
2. Command:
- List tags:
  git tag -l
- Lightweight tags
  git tag <tag-name> <commit-id>
- Annotated tag:
  git tag -a <tag-name> -m <msg> <commit-id>
- Share tag:
  git push <remote-repo> <tag-name>
- Share all tags:
  git push <remote-repo> --tags
- Delete tag:
  git tag -d <tag-name>
- Check out:
  git checkout <tag-name>
